Quote:  <i>Pomaderris elliptica (The Elliptical-leaved Pomaderris)..</i>. Native name, <i>Kumarahou</i>, from <i>Kumara, a tuber-like root, and hou, growing deep or strongly.</i> [Now much cultivated in New Zealand gardens.]
