Source:  Oxford Book of NZ Plants
Author:  MOORE & iRWiN
Vol / Page:  88
Edition:
Quote:  <i>POMADERRiS KUMERAHO</i>. Kumarahou is at home in the gumlands of Auckland, those broad tracts of hungry country where great kauri forests once grew, leaving deposits of resin - ... Flower heads rubbed between wet hands make a lather, hence the name `gumdiggers' soap'.
