Quote:  in the 1930s, kumarahou was heavily promoted by radio personality Aunt Daisy. "Old people and young ones with rheumatism or wheezing with asthma would come to the studio and the office girls would hand out portions of kumarahou," said Aunt Daisy, recalling her days on 1ZB.
